default, wellbeing or health inequalities? 
default&#xa0;
defaultNo significant impacts. 
default&#xa0;
default8.
default              
defaultHave the measures set out in the draft Bill been subject to adequate cost-benefit analysis on the basis of consultation with those affected? 
default&#xa0;
defaultA proposition and business case for the rail devolution proposals was submitted to the Department of Transport in August 2013.  It is currently under consideration.  It sets out the business case for the proposed changes according to Treasury guidelines on business cases.  
default&#xa0;
default9. 
default              
defaultWill any or all of the proposals have any significant economic or financial impact? Do you have any evidence of the impact that will aid the Committee in their scrutiny? 
default&#xa0;
defaultThe primary aim of our proposals is to achieve better economic outcomes from rail service provision by managing that provision more locally.  
